# Empty

A composable empty state for surfaces with nothing to show.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/empty
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([empty.outline()], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.icon([], [icon.box([])]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("No projects yet")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text(
          "Spin up your first project to start collecting traces and metrics.",
        ),
      ]),
    ]),
    empty.content([], [
      button.button([button.primary(), button.sm()], [
        html.text("Create project"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add empty
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/empty
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.icon([], [icon.file_text([])]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("No documents yet")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text("Create your first document to start writing."),
      ]),
    ]),
    empty.content([], [
      button.button([button.primary()], [html.text("New document")]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Variants

Two ways to frame the container, from a borderless ghost to a dashed outline.

### Ghost

Suited to empty states nested inside a card or panel that already supplies a frame.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/empty
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([empty.ghost()], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.icon([], [icon.box([])]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("No projects yet")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text("Spin up your first project to start collecting data."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Outline

Sets the region apart when the empty state stands on its own.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/empty
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([empty.outline()], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.icon([], [icon.box([])]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("No projects yet")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text("Spin up your first project to start collecting data."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Examples

Compose an empty state from header and content slots, varying media and actions to suit.

### Icon

Render a tinted square tile sized for a single icon child using the icon element.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/empty
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([empty.outline()], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.icon([], [icon.search([])]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("No matching results")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text("Try a different keyword or clear your filters."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Media

Place an image inside a media element for an avatar or illustration.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/empty

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.media([], [
        html.img([
          attribute.src("/img/avatar.jpg"),
          attribute.alt("Your profile photo"),
          attribute.class("size-12 rounded-full"),
        ]),
      ]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("No recent activity")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text(
          "You haven't opened a dashboard in a while.
          Pick up where you left off.",
        ),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Actions

Drop an action into the content element to point the user at the next step.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/empty
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([empty.outline()], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.icon([], [icon.user([])]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("No team members")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text("Invite your teammates to start collaborating on projects."),
      ]),
    ]),
    empty.content([], [
      button.button([button.primary(), button.sm()], [
        html.text("Invite people"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Rich Content

Stack multiple actions inside the content element and pair them with helper text or links.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/empty
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([empty.outline()], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.icon([], [icon.box([])]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("No items in this collection")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text(
          "Add an item from your library or import a CSV to get started.",
        ),
      ]),
    ]),
    empty.content([], [
      html.div([attribute.class("flex gap-2")], [
        button.button([button.primary(), button.sm()], [html.text("Add item")]),
        button.button([button.outline(), button.sm()], [
          html.text("Import CSV"),
        ]),
      ]),
      html.p([attribute.class("text-xs text-muted-foreground")], [
        html.text("Need help? "),
        html.a([attribute.href("#")], [html.text("Read the docs")]),
        html.text("."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Variants

Sets how the container is framed. Pass one into the root's attribute list.

| Variant | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `empty.ghost()` | The default borderless surface, for empty states a card or panel already frames. |
| `empty.outline()` | Frames the surface with a dashed border. |

### Elements

The root element and slots that compose its body.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `empty.root(attrs, children)` | Surface container. |
| `empty.header(attrs, children)` | Top region grouping the optional media or icon, title, and description. |
| `empty.media(attrs, children)` | Transparent slot for illustrations or larger imagery. |
| `empty.icon(attrs, children)` | Tinted square tile sized for a single decorative icon. |
| `empty.title(attrs, children)` | Primary heading inside the header. |
| `empty.description(attrs, children)` | Secondary supporting text inside the header. |
| `empty.content(attrs, children)` | Body region below the header for actions, links, or supporting copy. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the empty state's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="empty"]` | The root container. |
| `[data-slot="empty"][data-variant="ghost\|outline"]` | The root, tagged with its active framing. |
| `[data-slot="empty-header"]` | The header region of the container. |
| `[data-slot="empty-media"]` | The transparent media slot. |
| `[data-slot="empty-icon"]` | The tinted square media slot. |
| `[data-slot="empty-title"]` | The title row inside the header. |
| `[data-slot="empty-description"]` | The description row inside the header. |
| `[data-slot="empty-content"]` | The content region below the header. |

## Accessibility

**Plain container semantics.** Empty states render as plain containers, so they carry no landmark role. Place them inside the surrounding region (a list, a panel, a section) that already announces context to assistive tech.

